author: JEREMY WOZNICK Sports Reporter jwoznick@starherald.com
title: Holloway leads Scottsbluff golfers to GNAC title
text:
World-Herald News Service Holloway leads Scottsbluff golfers to GNAC title 
Scottsbluff's Hannah Holloway putts during the GNAC Tournament on Friday in North Platte. Holloway won the individual title and the Bearcats claimed the team championship. Posted: Friday, October 2, 2015 8:27 pm Holloway leads Scottsbluff golfers to GNAC title JEREMY WOZNICK Sports Reporter jwoznick@starherald.com Star Herald NORTH PLATTE — Not wind, rain, a 90-minute delay, or a one-hole playoff could keep Scottsbluff senior Hannah Holloway from winning her first Greater Nebraska Athletic Conference Tournament title on Friday at Lake Maloney Golf Club in North Platte. Holloway overcame all of those obstacles to card a winning score of 84.
